# Tell Vercel what NOT to bundle. The Vercel deploy now serves:
#   • /api/mark, /api/todo  — webhook handlers (existing)
#   • /api/tick             — cron-driven nudger (existing)
#   • /api/render           — live dashboard render (NEW)
#
# render.py IS bundled now (imported by /api/render). Everything else still
# lives elsewhere:
#   - the dashboard's static index.html lives on GitHub Pages (fallback only)
#   - tick.py runs on GitHub Actions, not Vercel
#   - data files (goals.yaml, settings.yaml, state/, etc.) are read at runtime
#     via the GitHub Contents API, not bundled into the Vercel deploy

tick.py
goals.yaml
settings.example.yaml
state/
index.html
analytics.html
style.css
*.md
*.zip
.github/
design_handoff_life_tracker/
